        "title": "Why won&#39;t my program run what is in the loop in java?",
        "body": "<p>My issue here is that I want it to print all four cities listed, but instead it will only print Toronto. <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Test\n{\n  public static void main(String[] args)\n  {\n    String[] allowed = new String[] {\"New York\", \"Singapore\", \"Paris\", \"Toronto\"};\n\n    int index;\n    for(index=0; index &lt; allowed.length - 1; index++);\n    {\n      System.out.println(allowed[index]);\n    }\n  }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>If I run it without the \"- 1\" after the allowed.length, I get an out of bounds error. I tried converting it to a while loop as well, and still no luck. What am I missing regarding my loop?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 26718580,
